  "body": "The fast-sync is composed of two steps: \r\n1. Fetch/store chain data (headers, bodies and receipts), in batches, until we are in sync with the network\r\n2. Fetch/store state data by requesting all missing trie nodes starting from the current head's state_root\r\n\r\nRight now, step 1 advances our chain head for every batch it downloads/stores, so if we don't complete step 2 we're left with a DB in an inconsistent state as we won't have the state for the current head.\r\n\r\nOne easy way to workaround that is to check (in `FullNodeSyncer`) if we have the state for the current head before running a regular sync, and, if not run the `StateDownloader` before starting the regular sync.",
